Path: docs/codegraph/ARCHITECTURE.md
 1	# Codegraph Architecture
 2	
 3	This document describes the architecture and design principles of the Codegraph module in TekAIContextEngine2.
 4	
 5	## Overview
 6	
 7	The Codegraph module is designed to provide comprehensive code analysis and indexing capabilities by combining multiple complementary technologies:
 8	
 9	1. **SCIP (SCIP Code Intelligence Protocol)** - Semantic analysis and symbol relationships
 10	2. **Tree-sitter** - Fast, incremental parsing for structural analysis
 11	3. **Vector Embeddings** - Semantic search and similarity matching
 12	4. **BadgerDB** - High-performance storage for indexed data
 13	
 14	## System Architecture
 15	
 16	```mermaid
 17	graph TB
 18	 subgraph "Client Layer"
 19	 API[REST API]
 20	 WS[WebSocket]
 21	 Health[Health Checks]
 22	 end
 23	
 24	 subgraph "Service Layer"
 25	 CS[Codegraph Service]
 26	 CCS[Config Service]
 27	 STS[SCIP Tools Service]
 28	 CMS[Metrics Service]
 29	 end
 30	
 31	 subgraph "Processing Layer"
 32	 CP[Codegraph Processor]
 33	 SS[SCIP Service]
 34	 TSS[Tree-sitter Service]
 35	 ES[Embedding Service]
 36	 end
 37	
 38	 subgraph "Storage Layer"
 39	 BDS[BadgerDB Service]
 40	 PS[Prisma/PostgreSQL]
 41	 FS[File Storage]
 42	 end
 43	
 44	 subgraph "External Tools"
 45	 ST[SCIP Tools]
 46	 TS[Tree-sitter Parsers]
 47	 EM[Embedding Models]
 48	 end
 49	
 50	 API --> CS
 51	 WS --> CP
 52	 Health --> CMS
 53	 
 54	 CS --> CP
 55	 CS --> CCS
 56	 CS --> STS
 57	 
 58	 CP --> SS
 59	 CP --> TSS
 60	 CP --> ES
 61	 
 62	 SS --> ST
 63	 TSS --> TS
 64	 ES --> EM
 65	 
 66	 SS --> BDS
 67	 TSS --> BDS
 68	 ES --> PS
 69	 
 70	 CS --> PS
 71	 CP --> FS
 72	```
