 295	## Quality Checklist for Each Module
 296	
 297	### Before Starting
 298	- [ ] Read all related documentation
 299	- [ ] Understand dependencies
 300	- [ ] Review integration points
 301	- [ ] Plan test strategy
 302	
 303	### During Implementation
 304	- [ ] Write comprehensive docstrings
 305	- [ ] Add inline comments for "why" not "what"
 306	- [ ] Create tests alongside implementation
 307	- [ ] Consider error cases explicitly
 308	- [ ] Think about performance implications
 309	- [ ] Document design decisions
 310	
 311	### After Implementation
 312	- [ ] All tests passing
 313	- [ ] Code coverage > 80%
 314	- [ ] Documentation complete
 315	- [ ] Performance benchmarks met
 316	- [ ] Integration tests written
 317	- [ ] Edge cases handled
 318	- [ ] Error messages helpful
 319	- [ ] Logging appropriate
 320	
 321	## Common Patterns to Follow
 322	
 323	### 1. Dependency Injection
 324	```typescript
 325	// Always inject dependencies for testability
 326	constructor(
 327	 private readonly config: Config,
 328	 private readonly logger: ILogger,
 329	 private readonly storage: IStorage
 330	) {
 331	 // Validate required dependencies
 332	 this.validateDependencies();
 333	}
 334	```
 335	
 336	### 2. Error Handling
 337	```typescript
 338	// Provide context in errors
 339	throw new ModuleError(
 340	 `Failed to process ${inputType}`,
 341	 { 
 342	 module: this.name,
 343	 operation: 'process',
 344	 input: sanitizedInput,
 345	 cause: originalError 
 346	 }
 347	);
 348	```
 349	
 350	### 3. Async Resource Management
 351	```typescript
 352	// Always clean up resources
 353	const resource = await this.acquire();
 354	try {
 355	 return await this.process(resource);
 356	} finally {
 357	 await this.release(resource);
 358	}
 359	```
 360	
 361	### 4. State Management
 362	```typescript
 363	// Make state transitions explicit
 364	private async transitionTo(newState: State): Promise<void> {
 365	 const oldState = this.state;
 366	 
 367	 // Validate transition
 368	 if (!this.isValidTransition(oldState, newState)) {
 369	 throw new InvalidStateTransition(oldState, newState);
 370	 }
 371	 
 372	 // Update state
 373	 this.state = newState;
 374	 
 375	 // Emit event
 376	 await this.emit('stateChanged', { oldState, newState });
 377	}
 378	```
 379	
 380	## Remember: Core Principles
 381	
 382	1. **We Do The Hard Work**: No shortcuts. Every edge case matters.
 383	2. **Comments Teach**: Future developers (including future us) need to understand why.
 384	3. **Tests Document Behavior**: Tests are executable documentation.
 385	4. **Errors Guide Users**: Every error should help the user fix the problem.
 386	5. **Performance Matters**: Measure, optimize, document.
 387	6. **Security First**: Never trust input. Always validate. Sanitize output.
 388	
