 667	### Step 8: Usage Examples
 668	
 669	```typescript
 670	// Example: Using Langfuse module in an agent
 671	class MyAgent {
 672	 private langfuse: ILangfuseModule;
 673	 
 674	 async execute(input: any): Promise<any> {
 675	 // Tracing is automatic if context exists
 676	 const span = this.langfuse.getCurrentTrace()?.span({
 677	 name: 'agent-execution',
 678	 input
 679	 });
 680	 
 681	 try {
 682	 // Do work
 683	 const result = await this.doWork(input);
 684	 
 685	 span?.update({ output: result });
 686	 span?.end({ level: 'DEFAULT' });
 687	 
 688	 return result;
 689	 } catch (error) {
 690	 span?.end({ 
 691	 level: 'ERROR',
 692	 statusMessage: error.message 
 693	 });
 694	 throw error;
 695	 }
 696	 }
 697	}
 698	```
 699	
 700	## Post-Implementation Validation
 701	
 702	### 1. Functionality Checklist
 703	- [ ] Context propagation works across async calls
 704	- [ ] Nested spans work correctly
 705	- [ ] Data sanitization removes sensitive info
 706	- [ ] Sampling works as configured
 707	- [ ] No-op mode has zero overhead
 708	- [ ] Flushing works reliably
 709	
 710	### 2. Security Requirements
 711	- [ ] All sensitive data is redacted
 712	- [ ] User IDs can be anonymized
 713	- [ ] Metadata filtering works
 714	- [ ] No secrets in traces
 715	
 716	### 3. Performance Requirements
 717	- [ ] Minimal overhead when enabled
 718	- [ ] Zero overhead when disabled
 719	- [ ] No memory leaks from context
 720	- [ ] Efficient batching
 721	
 722	## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
 723	
 724	1. **Don't expose raw Langfuse objects** - Always wrap them
 725	2. **Don't forget context cleanup** - Prevent memory leaks
 726	3. **Don't trace sensitive data** - Always sanitize
 727	4. **Don't block on flush** - Use async operations
 728	5. **Don't ignore sampling** - Important for high-volume apps
 729	6. **Don't create spans without ending them** - Memory leak risk
 730	
 731	## Final Validation Questions
 732	
 733	1. Is context propagation automatic and reliable?
 734	2. Does data sanitization catch all sensitive patterns?
 735	3. Is the module truly independent?
 736	4. Does it handle Langfuse SDK errors gracefully?
 737	5. Is performance impact acceptable?
 738	6. Can developers use it without understanding Langfuse?
 739	
 740	## Next Steps
 741	After completing the Langfuse module, implement the Session & State module (03-session-state-module-implementation.md) for centralized state management.
