 1	# AgentHub: Revised Modular Architecture
 2	
 3	## Overview
 4	
 5	AgentHub is designed as a **modular system** where each major capability is encapsulated in its own module, with the AgentHub core orchestrating and controlling access to these modules through careful wrapping and abstraction.
 6	
 7	## Core Architecture
 8	
 9	```
 10	┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 11	│ AgentHub Core │
 12	│ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │
 13	│ │ Module Registry │ │
 14	│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │
 15	│ │
 16	│ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌───────────────────┐ │
 17	│ │ LiteLLM │ │ Langfuse │ │ Session & State │ │
 18	│ │ Module │ │ Module │ │ Module │ │
 19	│ │ (Proxy API) │ │ (Wrapped) │ │ (Centralized) │ │
 20	│ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └───────────────────┘ │
 21	│ │
 22	│ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌───────────────────┐ │
 23	│ │ Memory │ │ Tools │ │ Monitoring │ │
 24	│ │ Module │ │ Module │ │ Module │ │
 25	│ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └───────────────────┘ │
 26	└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 27	
 28	 ▼
 29	 Agent Type Modules
 30	┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
 31	│ LLM Agent │ │ Workflow │ │ Custom │
 32	│ Module │ │ Agents │ │ Agents │
 33	└──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘
 34	```
 35	
 36	## Module Design Principles
 37	
 38	### 1. Each Module is Self-Contained
 39	- Has its own interfaces
 40	- Manages its own configuration
 41	- Handles its own errors
 42	- Provides its own monitoring hooks
 43	
 44	### 2. Controlled Access Through Wrapping
 45	- No direct access to third-party libraries
 46	- All interactions go through module interfaces
 47	- Consistent error handling and logging
 48	- Ability to swap implementations
 49	
 50	### 3. Centralized Control
 51	- AgentHub core controls module lifecycle
 52	- Unified configuration management
 53	- Consistent authentication/authorization
 54	- Centralized monitoring and metrics
 55	
 56	## Core Modules
 57	
 58	### 1. LiteLLM Module (Python Proxy Integration)
 59	
 60	Since LiteLLM is Python-based, we'll use the LiteLLM proxy server:
 61	
 62	```typescript
 63	// modules/litellm/index.ts
 64	export interface ILiteLLMModule {
 65	 initialize(config: LiteLLMConfig): Promise<void>;
 66	 complete(request: LLMRequest): Promise<LLMResponse>;
 67	 stream(request: LLMRequest): AsyncIterator<LLMChunk>;
 68	 health(): Promise<HealthStatus>;
 69	}
 70	
 71	class LiteLLMModule implements ILiteLLMModule {
 72	 private proxyClient: LiteLLMProxyClient;
 73	 private config: LiteLLMConfig;
 74	 
 75	 async initialize(config: LiteLLMConfig): Promise<void> {
 76	 // Connect to LiteLLM proxy server
 77	 this.proxyClient = new LiteLLMProxyClient({
 78	 baseUrl: config.proxyUrl || 'http://localhost:8000',
 79	 apiKey: config.proxyApiKey,
 80	 timeout: config.timeout
 81	 });
 82	 
 83	 // Verify connection
 84	 await this.proxyClient.healthCheck();
 85	 }
 86	 
 87	 async complete(request: LLMRequest): Promise<LLMResponse> {
 88	 // All LLM calls go through the proxy
 89	 // The proxy handles:
 90	 // - Model routing
 91	 // - Fallbacks
 92	 // - Rate limiting
 93	 // - Cost tracking
 94	 
 95	 const proxyRequest = this.transformRequest(request);
 96	 const response = await this.proxyClient.post('/chat/completions', proxyRequest);
 97	 return this.transformResponse(response);
 98	 }
 99	}
 100	
 101	// Module factory
 102	export function createLiteLLMModule(config: LiteLLMConfig): ILiteLLMModule {
 103	 const module = new LiteLLMModule();
 104	 return wrapModule(module, 'litellm'); // Wrapping for monitoring/logging
 105	}
 106	```
 107	
 108	**LiteLLM Proxy Server Configuration:**
 109	```yaml
 110	# litellm_config.yaml
 111	model_list:
 112	 - model_name: "gpt-4"
 113	 litellm_params:
 114	 model: "openai/gpt-4"
 115	 api_key: "os.environ/OPENAI_API_KEY"
 116	 
 117	 - model_name: "claude-3"
 118	 litellm_params:
 119	 model: "anthropic/claude-3-opus"
 120	 api_key: "os.environ/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY"
 121	
 122	router_settings:
 123	 routing_strategy: "usage-based"
 124	 fallbacks:
 125	 gpt-4: ["claude-3", "gpt-3.5-turbo"]
 126	 
 127	 retry_policy:
 128	 max_retries: 3
 129	 retry_after: 5
 130	```
 131	
 132	### 2. Langfuse Module (Wrapped Integration)
 133	
 134	```typescript
 135	// modules/langfuse/index.ts
 136	export interface ILangfuseModule {
 137	 initialize(config: LangfuseConfig): Promise<void>;
 138	 startTrace(name: string, metadata?: any): ITrace;
 139	 span(name: string, fn: () => Promise<any>): Promise<any>;
 140	 flush(): Promise<void>;
 141	}
 142	
 143	class LangfuseModule implements ILangfuseModule {
 144	 private client: Langfuse;
 145	 private contextManager: TraceContextManager;
 146	 
 147	 async initialize(config: LangfuseConfig): Promise<void> {
 148	 this.client = new Langfuse({
 149	 publicKey: config.publicKey,
 150	 secretKey: config.secretKey,
 151	 baseUrl: config.baseUrl
 152	 });
 153	 
 154	 this.contextManager = new TraceContextManager();
 155	 }
 156	 
 157	 startTrace(name: string, metadata?: any): ITrace {
 158	 const trace = this.client.trace({ name, metadata });
 159	 
 160	 // Wrap the trace object to control access
 161	 return new WrappedTrace(trace, this.contextManager);
 162	 }
 163	}
 164	
 165	// Wrapped trace to control access
 166	class WrappedTrace implements ITrace {
 167	 constructor(
 168	 private trace: LangfuseTrace,
 169	 private contextManager: TraceContextManager
 170	 ) {}
 171	 
 172	 span(name: string): ISpan {
 173	 const span = this.trace.span({ name });
 174	 this.contextManager.setCurrentSpan(span);
 175	 return new WrappedSpan(span);
 176	 }
 177	 
 178	 // Control what methods are exposed
 179	 update(data: any): void {
 180	 // Add validation, sanitization, etc.
 181	 this.trace.update(this.sanitize(data));
 182	 }
 183	}
 184	```
 185	
 186	### 3. Session & State Management Module
 187	
 188	This is a **centralized module** for all state and session management:
 189	
 190	```typescript
 191	// modules/session-state/index.ts
 192	export interface ISessionStateModule {
 193	 // Session Management
 194	 createSession(userId?: string): Promise<Session>;
 195	 getSession(sessionId: string): Promise<Session>;
 196	 updateSession(sessionId: string, updates: any): Promise<void>;
 197	 
 198	 // State Management
 199	 getState(scope: StateScope): Promise<State>;
 200	 setState(scope: StateScope, key: string, value: any): Promise<void>;
 201	 
 202	 // Memory Management
 203	 addMemory(sessionId: string, memory: Memory): Promise<void>;
 204	 queryMemory(sessionId: string, query: string): Promise<Memory[]>;
 205	 
 206	 // Persistence
 207	 checkpoint(sessionId: string): Promise<string>;
 208	 restore(checkpointId: string): Promise<Session>;
 209	}
 210	
 211	class SessionStateModule implements ISessionStateModule {
 212	 private sessionStore: ISessionStore;
 213	 private stateManager: IStateManager;
 214	 private memoryService: IMemoryService;
 215	 
 216	 constructor(config: SessionStateConfig) {
 217	 // Initialize stores based on config
 218	 this.sessionStore = this.createSessionStore(config.session);
 219	 this.stateManager = this.createStateManager(config.state);
 220	 this.memoryService = this.createMemoryService(config.memory);
 221	 }
 222	 
 223	 async createSession(userId?: string): Promise<Session> {
 224	 const session = new Session({
 225	 id: generateId(),
 226	 userId,
 227	 createdAt: Date.now(),
 228	 state: this.stateManager.createInitialState()
 229	 });
 230	 
 231	 await this.sessionStore.save(session);
 232	 return session;
 233	 }
 234	 
 235	 // Centralized state access with scoping
 236	 async getState(scope: StateScope): Promise<State> {
 237	 switch (scope.type) {
 238	 case 'session':
 239	 return this.stateManager.getSessionState(scope.sessionId);
 240	 
 241	 case 'user':
 242	 return this.stateManager.getUserState(scope.userId);
 243	 
 244	 case 'global':
 245	 return this.stateManager.getGlobalState();
 246	 
 247	 case 'agent':
 248	 return this.stateManager.getAgentState(scope.agentId);
 249	 }
 250	 }
 251	}
 252	
 253	// State scoping
 254	export interface StateScope {
 255	 type: 'session' | 'user' | 'global' | 'agent';
 256	 sessionId?: string;
 257	 userId?: string;
 258	 agentId?: string;
 259	}
 260	```
 261	
 262	### 4. Memory Module
 263	
 264	Separate module for memory management:
 265	
 266	```typescript
 267	// modules/memory/index.ts
 268	export interface IMemoryModule {
 269	 initialize(config: MemoryConfig): Promise<void>;
 270	 
 271	 // Short-term memory
 272	 addWorkingMemory(item: MemoryItem): Promise<void>;
 273	 getWorkingMemory(limit?: number): Promise<MemoryItem[]>;
 274	 
 275	 // Long-term memory
 276	 store(key: string, value: any, ttl?: number): Promise<void>;
 277	 retrieve(query: string): Promise<MemoryResult[]>;
 278	 
 279	 // Vector operations
 280	 embed(text: string): Promise<number[]>;
 281	 search(embedding: number[], limit?: number): Promise<SearchResult[]>;
 282	}
 283	
 284	class MemoryModule implements IMemoryModule {
 285	 private workingMemory: WorkingMemory;
 286	 private vectorStore: IVectorStore;
 287	 private embedder: IEmbedder;
 288	 
 289	 async initialize(config: MemoryConfig): Promise<void> {
 290	 this.workingMemory = new WorkingMemory(config.workingMemory);
 291	 this.vectorStore = await this.createVectorStore(config.vectorStore);
 292	 this.embedder = await this.createEmbedder(config.embedding);
 293	 }
 294	}
 295	```
 296	
 297	### 5. Tools Module
 298	
 299	Centralized tool management:
 300	
 301	```typescript
 302	// modules/tools/index.ts
 303	export interface IToolsModule {
 304	 register(tool: ITool): void;
 305	 execute(toolName: string, args: any): Promise<any>;
 306	 list(): ToolInfo[];
 307	 validate(toolName: string, args: any): ValidationResult;
 308	}
 309	
 310	class ToolsModule implements IToolsModule {
 311	 private tools = new Map<string, ITool>();
 312	 private executor: ToolExecutor;
 313	 
 314	 register(tool: ITool): void {
 315	 // Validate tool interface
 316	 this.validateTool(tool);
 317	 
 318	 // Wrap tool for monitoring
 319	 const wrapped = this.wrapTool(tool);
 320	 
 321	 this.tools.set(tool.name, wrapped);
 322	 }
 323	 
 324	 private wrapTool(tool: ITool): ITool {
 325	 return {
 326	 ...tool,
 327	 execute: async (args: any) => {
 328	 const span = this.tracer.startSpan(`tool.${tool.name}`);
 329	 
 330	 try {
 331	 // Pre-execution validation
 332	 await this.preExecute(tool, args);
 333	 
 334	 // Execute with timeout
 335	 const result = await this.withTimeout(
 336	 tool.execute(args),
 337	 tool.timeout || 30000
 338	 );
 339	 
 340	 // Post-execution validation
 341	 await this.postExecute(tool, result);
 342	 
 343	 return result;
 344	 } catch (error) {
 345	 span.recordException(error);
 346	 throw error;
 347	 } finally {
 348	 span.end();
 349	 }
 350	 }
 351	 };
 352	 }
 353	}
 354	```
 355	
 356	## Module Integration in AgentHub
 357	
 358	```typescript
 359	// agenthub/core.ts
 360	export class AgentHub {
 361	 private modules: ModuleRegistry;
 362	 
 363	 private constructor(config: AgentHubConfig) {
 364	 this.modules = new ModuleRegistry();
 365	 
 366	 // Initialize core modules
 367	 this.initializeCoreModules(config);
 368	 }
 369	 
 370	 private async initializeCoreModules(config: AgentHubConfig): Promise<void> {
 371	 // LiteLLM Module (connects to proxy)
 372	 const litellm = createLiteLLMModule(config.litellm);
 373	 await litellm.initialize(config.litellm);
 374	 this.modules.register('litellm', litellm);
 375	 
 376	 // Langfuse Module (wrapped)
 377	 const langfuse = createLangfuseModule(config.langfuse);
 378	 await langfuse.initialize(config.langfuse);
 379	 this.modules.register('langfuse', langfuse);
 380	 
 381	 // Session & State Module (centralized)
 382	 const sessionState = createSessionStateModule(config.sessionState);
 383	 await sessionState.initialize(config.sessionState);
 384	 this.modules.register('sessionState', sessionState);
 385	 
 386	 // Memory Module
 387	 const memory = createMemoryModule(config.memory);
 388	 await memory.initialize(config.memory);
 389	 this.modules.register('memory', memory);
 390	 
 391	 // Tools Module
 392	 const tools = createToolsModule(config.tools);
 393	 await tools.initialize(config.tools);
 394	 this.modules.register('tools', tools);
 395	 }
 396	 
 397	 // Controlled access to modules
 398	 getModule<T>(name: string): T {
 399	 const module = this.modules.get(name);
 400	 if (!module) {
 401	 throw new Error(`Module '${name}' not found`);
 402	 }
 403	 
 404	 // Return wrapped module for additional control
 405	 return this.wrapModuleAccess(module) as T;
 406	 }
 407	}
 408	```
 409	
 410	## Benefits of This Architecture
 411	
 412	### 1. True Modularity
 413	- Each capability is a separate module
 414	- Modules can be developed/tested independently
 415	- Easy to add new modules
 416	
 417	### 2. Controlled Access
 418	- No direct access to third-party libraries
 419	- All interactions go through module interfaces
 420	- Consistent error handling across modules
 421	
 422	### 3. Centralized Management
 423	- Session/state management in one place
 424	- Unified configuration
 425	- Consistent monitoring/logging
 426	
 427	### 4. Flexibility
 428	- Easy to swap implementations
 429	- Can use different backends for each module
 430	- Gradual migration possible
 431	
 432	### 5. Testability
 433	- Each module can be mocked
 434	- Integration tests at module boundaries
 435	- Clear separation of concerns
 436	
 437	## Example: Creating an Agent with Modules
 438	
 439	```typescript
 440	class LLMAgent extends BaseAgent {
 441	 private litellm: ILiteLLMModule;
 442	 private sessionState: ISessionStateModule;
 443	 private memory: IMemoryModule;
 444	 
 445	 constructor(config: LLMAgentConfig) {
 446	 super(config);
 447	 
 448	 // Get modules from hub
 449	 const hub = AgentHub.getInstance();
 450	 this.litellm = hub.getModule<ILiteLLMModule>('litellm');
 451	 this.sessionState = hub.getModule<ISessionStateModule>('sessionState');
 452	 this.memory = hub.getModule<IMemoryModule>('memory');
 453	 }
 454	 
 455	 async execute(input: AgentInput): Promise<AgentOutput> {
 456	 // Get session
 457	 const session = await this.sessionState.getSession(input.sessionId);
 458	 
 459	 // Get conversation memory
 460	 const memories = await this.memory.getWorkingMemory();
 461	 
 462	 // Make LLM call through module
 463	 const response = await this.litellm.complete({
 464	 messages: this.buildMessages(input, memories),
 465	 model: this.config.model
 466	 });
 467	 
 468	 // Update state
 469	 await this.sessionState.setState(
 470	 { type: 'session', sessionId: session.id },
 471	 'lastResponse',
 472	 response
 473	 );
 474	 
 475	 // Add to memory
 476	 await this.memory.addWorkingMemory({
 477	 role: 'assistant',
 478	 content: response.content
 479	 });
 480	 
 481	 return { content: response.content };
 482	 }
 483	}
 484	```
 485	
 486	## Module Development Guidelines
 487	
 488	### 1. Module Interface
 489	Every module must implement:
 490	```typescript
 491	interface IModule {
 492	 name: string;
 493	 version: string;
 494	 initialize(config: any): Promise<void>;
 495	 health(): Promise<HealthStatus>;
 496	 shutdown(): Promise<void>;
 497	}
 498	```
 499	
 500	### 2. Module Factory
 501	Every module should have a factory function:
 502	```typescript
 503	export function createXModule(config: XConfig): IXModule {
 504	 const module = new XModule();
 505	 return wrapModule(module, 'x-module');
 506	}
 507	```
 508	
 509	### 3. Error Handling
 510	Modules should throw typed errors:
 511	```typescript
 512	export class ModuleError extends Error {
 513	 constructor(
 514	 public module: string,
 515	 public code: string,
 516	 message: string
 517	 ) {
 518	 super(message);
 519	 }
 520	}
 521	```
 522	
 523	This modular architecture ensures clean separation of concerns, controlled access to external dependencies, and centralized management of critical functions like session and state management.
