 10	// ❌ Wrong: Exposing complexity
 11	const agent = new LLMAgent({
 12	 llmProvider: new LiteLLM({...}),
 13	 tracer: new LangfuseTracer({...}),
 14	 memory: new ConversationMemory({...}),
 15	 stateManager: new StateManager({...})
 16	});
 17	
 18	// ✅ Right: Hiding complexity
 19	const agent = AgentHub.createAgent({
 20	 type: 'llm',
 21	 name: 'assistant',
 22	 instruction: 'You are a helpful assistant'
 23	});
 24	```
 25	
 26	### 2. Deep Thinking Before Coding
 27	- **Read First**: Documentation, existing code, related issues
 28	- **Understand Why**: Every feature has a purpose
 29	- **Plan Thoroughly**: Design before implementing
 30	- **Consider Edge Cases**: What could go wrong?
 31	
 32	### 3. Comments Are Teaching Tools
 33	```typescript
 34	// ❌ Wrong: Explaining what
 35	// Increment counter by 1
 36	counter++;
 37	
 38	// ✅ Right: Explaining why
 39	// Increment retry counter to track failed attempts for exponential backoff
 40	// This prevents overwhelming the service while giving transient errors time to resolve
 41	counter++;
 42	```
 43	
 44	### 4. Tests Are Living Documentation
 45	```typescript
 46	describe('LLMAgent', () => {
 47	 it('should resume conversation from checkpoint after crash', async () => {
 48	 // This test documents our resilience guarantee:
 49	 // Users never lose conversation progress even if the system crashes
 50	 
 51	 // Setup: Create conversation with history
 52	 const agent = createAgent();
 53	 await agent.execute({ input: 'Hello' });
 54	 await agent.execute({ input: 'Tell me about Paris' });
 55	 
 56	 // Simulate crash and recovery
 57	 const checkpointId = await agent.checkpoint();
 58	 const newAgent = createAgent();
 59	 await newAgent.resumeFrom(checkpointId);
 60	 
 61	 // Verify: Conversation continues seamlessly
 62	 const response = await newAgent.execute({ 
 63	 input: 'What did I ask about?' 
 64	 });
 65	 expect(response.output).toContain('Paris');
 66	 });
 67	});
 68	```
